This solution uses a stack to handle nested parentheses and a dictionary to count the occurrences of each atom. The `parse` function processes the formula string, updating the stack as it encounters opening and closing parentheses, and counting atoms and their multipliers. Finally, the atom counts are formatted into the required string format.
